cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.IT 

The paper discusses learning hidden structure and causal mechanisms from sample data, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of graphical models also suggests a potential fit for the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper may fall under the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT) due to the focus on exact inference and noisy networks.
